    <note type="biography">
        <p>German physiologist. Anatomical prosector at Königsberg University and self-taught physiologist. Professor of physiology, Halle, 1870; Straßburg (Strasbourg), 1872. Worked on reflex processes and the localisation of cerebral function in dogs; kept dogs without cerebrums alive for up to three years.</p>
